Richie Benaud died on Friday at the age of 84  . 
  The cricket commentator revealed he had skin cancer and was receiving radiation treatment . 
  He said he was receiving treatment for skin cancers on his forehead and the top of his head . 
  The 84-year-old said he never wore a cap as a kid in Australia . 
  Benaud said he believed the cancers were caused by playing cricket in the sun without a cap . 
  He was in a car accident in October 2013 and had not returned to his commentary job for the Nine Network . 
  He spoke about his cancer and the treatment he was undergoing last year . 
 